      <h2>InkFlow — Best Overall for Tattoo Studios</h2>
      <p>InkFlow is the only waiver app purpose-built for tattoo studios with native iPad optimization. It integrates waivers with booking, CRM, payments, and aftercare — one platform replaces four separate tools.</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Studios that want an all-in-one solution (waivers + booking + CRM + payments).</p>
      <p><strong>iPad experience:</strong> Clients sign directly on the iPad at check-in. Forms are stored with timestamp and IP log. Waivers auto-send at booking so clients can also sign from home.</p>

      <h2>WaiverSign — Best Standalone Waiver Tool</h2>
      <p>WaiverSign is a dedicated waiver platform with strong iPad browser support. It offers good e-signature features and QR check-in.</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Studios that only need waivers and already have a separate booking system.</p>

      <h2>Jotform — Most Customizable</h2>
      <p>Jotform offers powerful form-building features with conditional logic and payment collection. Works on iPad via browser but lacks native optimization.</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Studios that need complex form logic and are comfortable building their own templates.</p>

      <h2>Tattoogenda — Integrated but EU-Focused</h2>
      <p>Tattoogenda offers waivers as part of their booking platform. Good features but iPad experience is browser-based and EU-focused compliance may not fit all US studios.</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> EU-based studios or those needing GDPR-compliant waivers.</p>

