      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <h3>Can I use my existing iPad for digital waivers?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Any iPad with a browser works. InkFlow is optimized for iPad Safari and Chrome — no app download needed. Set up a kiosk stand at your front desk and clients sign in under 30 seconds.</p>

      <h3>Are iPad digital waivers legally binding?</h3>
      <p>Yes. E-signatures are legally binding under the ESIGN Act (US), UETA, and eIDAS (EU), provided they include proper timestamping, IP logging, and consumer consent.</p>

      <h3>Do I need an iPad for each artist?</h3>
      <p>Not necessarily. One iPad at the front desk is enough for most studios. Clients sign waivers at check-in. For busier studios, one iPad per artist or per station keeps the flow smooth.</p>
